               <msContents>
                  <summary/>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i0">
                     <t:locus xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" from="1v" to="44r">1v-44r</t:locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT0049IHA#s17IHA">قران, Tenth ǧuz’ (10/30)</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">
                        <t:locus xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" target="#1v">-1v</t:locus>وَاعْلَمُوا أَنَّمَا غَنِمْتُمْ مِنْ شَيْءٍ فَأَنَّ لِلَّهِ خُمُسَهُ وَلِلرَّسُولِ <note>8:41</note>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <t:locus xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" target="#44r">-44r</t:locus>وَطَبَعَ اللَّهُ عَلَى قُلُوبِهِمْ فَهُمْ لَا يَعْلَمُونَ<note>9:93</note>
                     </explicit>
                     <note>8:41-9:93. Some words are divided into two different lines.
The “ḏāl” is written with the dot inside. Sometimes the catchword is only the first part of the first word in the next page, sometimes there is a repeated word and the catchword is the second word of the next page. In 3v-4r the catchword is jut the end of the word repeated over the first line of 4r. In 14r-15v, 32r-v and 35r-v the paper is different, but the text goes on normally.
The name of the scribe appears in mss. 4521D (37r) and 4521X (1v, 45v). The note stating that he is actually the scribe is in 4521X (45v).  </note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
